HEADWORD: Faluns
<hw>Fa`luns"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A series of strata, of the Middle Tertiary
period, of France, abounding in shells, and used by Lyell as the type of
his Miocene subdivision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

